# 05-API - API Development Rules

## API Rules Directory

This directory contains all API development rules for Agent Player.

## Files Structure

### Core API Files
- `rest-standards.mdc` - REST API implementation standards
- `authentication.mdc` - Authentication and authorization
- `validation.mdc` - Input validation rules
- `documentation.mdc` - API documentation standards
- `versioning.mdc` - API versioning strategies

## Purpose

Define API development standards for:
- RESTful API design
- Authentication mechanisms
- Input validation
- Error handling
- Documentation

## Rules Coverage
- 84+ API endpoints
- Authentication patterns
- Validation strategies
- Error handling
- Documentation requirements

## MANDATORY API Standards
- All endpoints must follow REST conventions
- Input validation required on all endpoints
- Proper HTTP status codes for responses
- JSON format for request/response bodies
- Authentication required for protected endpoints
- Rate limiting for all public endpoints
- Error handling with consistent error format
- API versioning in URL path (/api/v1/)
- Comprehensive API documentation
- Unit and integration tests for all endpoints

